The paper deals with a problem of preprocessing a string to efficiently answer queries about its shortest unique palindromic substrings. This problem involves data structures and algorithms for string processing, which are typically studied in the computer science subfields of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents an optimal solution, which involves techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
